lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
def lemmatize(data):
    text = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(word) for word in data]
    return data


Data['full_text'] = Data['full_text'].apply(lambda x: lemmatize(x))
In [116]:
#ASSIGNING THE POLARITY

def polarity(text):
    return TextBlob(text).polarity
Data['polarity'] = Data['full_text'].apply(polarity)
def sentiment(label):
    if label<0:
        return "Negetive"
    elif label == 0:
        return "Neutral"
    elif label>0:
        return "Positive"
Data['Sentiment'] = Data['polarity'].apply(sentiment)

In [131]:
custom_stop_words = ["checkin", "service", "arrived", "among", "terminal", "international", "apparently", "for", "comfortable"]
In [132]:
stop_words = text.ENGLISH_STOP_WORDS.union(custom_stop_words)
In [133]:
# Weightage of the words in the tweets
stop_words = [frozenset(stop_words)]
vectorizer = CountVectorizer(max_df = 0.95, min_df = 2, stop_words = stop_words)
x = vectorizer.fit_transform(negetive_reviwes)
# Lda model
num_topics = 6
lda = LatentDirichletAllocation(n_components = num_topics, random_state=1)
lda.fit(x)
Out[133]:
LatentDirichletAllocation(n_components=6, random_state=1)
In [134]:
num_top_words = 7
feature_names = vectorizer.get_feature_names_out()
topics=[]
In [135]:
# Extracting the topics from LDA model
for topic_idx, topic in enumerate(lda.components_):
    top_words_idx = topic.argsort()[:-num_top_words - 1:-1]
    top_words = [feature_names[i] for i in top_words_idx]
    topics.append(top_words)

for i, topic in enumerate(topics):
    print(f"Topic {i+1}: {',' .join(topic)}")

Topic 1: immigration,security,answering,help,person,like,allowed
Topic 2: immigration,security,answering,help,person,like,impounded
Topic 3: immigration,stamped,like,security,person,help,answering
Topic 4: money,asked,answering,help,impounded,immigration,security
Topic 5: authority,immigration,allowed,person,impounded,security,answering
Topic 6: immigration,security,answering,help,person,like,allowed

WordCloud¶

In [136]:
res = [' '.join(ele) for ele in topics]
text = ' '.join([word for word in res])
plt.figure(figsize=(20,15), facecolor='None')
wordcloud= WordCloud(max_words=500, width=1600, height=800).generate(text)
plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
plt.axis("off")
plt.title('Most frequent words in Negetive Tweets (Check-In)', fontsize=19)
plt.show()

1) Passpot Service Issues:

• Issues with the implementation of proper security and service in the immigration sector.

2) Waiting issues in passport:

• Long queues and slow security checks at the airport are causing passengers to miss their flights and experience delays.

• Waiting and checkin for the passport service causes havoc.
